    {
      "lc": 1,
      "type": "constructor",
      "id": [
        "langchain",
        "schema",
        "messages",
        "ToolMessage"
      ],
      "kwargs": {
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "{\"success\":true,\"process_rule_id\":\"J09B\",\"process_rule\":\"1. Make a copy of decision_table with TOURS starting with J09B named J09B_temp\\n2. Update the table with an additional empty column ENTSCHEIDUNG\\n3. Apply the following rules to the joined table:\\n    1. Count the number of EQUNR for every HAUS and set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \\\"KSA\\\" if there are less than 3 EQUNR. ELSE set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \\\"EVU\\\"\\n    2. SET all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 of 0 to \\\"EVU\\\"\\n    3. SET all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 500 - 599 to \\\"EVU\\\"\\n    4. SET all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 900 - 999 to \\\"EVU\\\"\\n    5. SET all houses with address area Wiblingwerde or Breckerfeld to \\\"EVU\\\"\\n4. JOIN this table with the EABLG table using INSTALLATION.\\n5. JOIN this table with the NET_MASTER table and the SALES_MASTER table using EQUNR.\\n6. Compare sales data and net data for these IDs:\\n    If sales data is there, take sales data and empty net data.\\n    Otherwise stay with net data and empty sales data.\\n7. Set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \\\"MANDATORY_READING\\\", for every EQUNR in EABL where both ISTABLART_TXT = \\\"Maschinelle Schätzung - SAP\\\" and the Record created on 2024 and ISTABLART_TXT = \\\"Maschinelle Schätzung - SAP\\\" and the Record created on 2023.\\n8. Export all MANDATORY_READING entries from the final table as CSV file named J09B_MANDATORY_READING including the columns: `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`\\n9. Send them to the internal team to mandatory.reading@provider.com\\n10. Export the final data except MANDATORY_READING entries from the table as CSV file named J09B including the columns: `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`\\n11. Send them to the EVU team to meter.readings@evu.com\\n12. Delete the temporary table after exporting the data.\"}",
            "id": "lc_a0649535-44b5-4bd4-993a-e74375ce4504"
          }
        ],
        "type": "tool",
        "name": "retrieve_process",
        "id": "00e97eb9-e2c4-4c16-ad43-95fbb58b3acc",
        "tool_call_id": "call_q3gpc4bq",
        "artifact": {
          "structured_content": {
            "success": true,
            "process_rule_id": "J09B",
            "process_rule": "1. Make a copy of decision_table with TOURS starting with J09B named J09B_temp\n2. Update the table with an additional empty column ENTSCHEIDUNG\n3. Apply the following rules to the joined table:\n    1. Count the number of EQUNR for every HAUS and set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \"KSA\" if there are less than 3 EQUNR. ELSE set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \"EVU\"\n    2. SET all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 of 0 to \"EVU\"\n    3. SET all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 500 - 599 to \"EVU\"\n    4. SET all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 900 - 999 to \"EVU\"\n    5. SET all houses with address area Wiblingwerde or Breckerfeld to \"EVU\"\n4. JOIN this table with the EABLG table using INSTALLATION.\n5. JOIN this table with the NET_MASTER table and the SALES_MASTER table using EQUNR.\n6. Compare sales data and net data for these IDs:\n    If sales data is there, take sales data and empty net data.\n    Otherwise stay with net data and empty sales data.\n7. Set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \"MANDATORY_READING\", for every EQUNR in EABL where both ISTABLART_TXT = \"Maschinelle Schätzung - SAP\" and the Record created on 2024 and ISTABLART_TXT = \"Maschinelle Schätzung - SAP\" and the Record created on 2023.\n8. Export all MANDATORY_READING entries from the final table as CSV file named J09B_MANDATORY_READING including the columns: `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`\n9. Send them to the internal team to mandatory.reading@provider.com\n10. Export the final data except MANDATORY_READING entries from the table as CSV file named J09B including the columns: `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`\n11. Send them to the EVU team to meter.readings@evu.com\n12. Delete the temporary table after exporting the data."
          }
        },
        "status": "success"
      }
    },
